* // ---------- Test Spy ---------- // *

# Observes interactions with tested code
    - Number of times called
    - How it was called
    - What it responded to

# Verifies indirect outputs
# Can add to existing or replace

Example:
    Validator was called once with transformed values

* // ---------- Sinon.JS Spies ---------- // *

Uses:
    - Record information about calls

# Can be anonymous
    - Use when not testing behaviour

# Can wrap existing methods
    - Behaves exactly like original method
    - Will record access data

! Testing Exported Named Functions !
    - When testing a named function in the same file...
    - Don't call FUNCTIONNAME in the target...
    - Use module.exports.FUNCTIONNAME
Example:
    module.exports.validate(reservation)
